Login Profile Image Fix

File:

Login.tsx

Problem:

The profile image existed in the backend but appeared broken or incomplete in navbars.

Cause:

The saved image path in localStorage could be relative.

Example:

/media/profile_images/image.jpg

Frontend img tags need full URL:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/media/profile_images/image.jpg

Fix:

normalizeUser() was updated.

New behavior:

If profile image starts with http:

Use it directly

If profile image is relative:

Prefix it with:

http://127.0.0.1:8000

Then store both:

profile_image
profile_image_url

inside localStorage.

Important Testing Note

After updating Login.tsx, the user must:

Logout
Login again

Reason:

localStorage still contains the old broken image path until new login refreshes stored user data.

