Security Notes

Frontend checks are only for UI behavior.

Real access control remains in backend.

Examples:

Student dashboard APIs use IsStudent
Course lessons check enrollment
Video token API checks permissions
Video lock APIs check user/session state
Purchase APIs require authentication

Frontend role checks do not replace backend security.

Errors Encountered During This Stage

1. Student Dashboard route did not exist

Solution:

Created new /student route using StudentLayout.

2. Old /dashboard/student route became outdated

Solution:

Replaced it with /student.

3. ProtectedRoute role check was unreliable

Cause:

Role could exist inside user object but not localStorage role.

Solution:

Parse user object and read role from it.

4. My Courses Enter Course redirected to Login

Cause:

CourseLessons checked access_token in localStorage.

Solution:

Removed localStorage token redirect logic.

5. Buy button redirected to Login

Cause:

SubjectCourses checked access_token.

Solution:

Changed login check to Boolean(user).

6. Subjects page showed Login/Register while logged in

Cause:

Subjects checked access_token.

Solution:

Changed login check to Boolean(user).

7. Profile image did not show globally

Cause:

Relative media URL was stored in localStorage.

Solution:

Normalize profile image URL during login.

8. ESLint warning no-useless-assignment

Cause:

A temporary variable was assigned but not used correctly in ProtectedRoute.

Solution:

Refactored parsing logic into parsedUser variable.

